When people think of their favorite cinematic versions of Superman, they tend to be split. Traditionalists will point to Christopher Reeve, and his series of films that made us "Believe A Man Could Fly". Others call the Reeve version "outdated", celebrating and favoring Henry Cavill's Man of Steel above all others. Right in the middle, sits Brandon Routh and his portrayal of the Big Blue Boy Scout in Superman Returns. Join us as we look back 15 years at the film that was set to take Superman to new heights before the DCEU even existed!

